---
const steps = [
  {
    number: '01',
    title: 'Define the problem',
    body: 'Start with a goal\u2014not a prompt. The system guides you through problem definition and generates a structured PRD, catching gaps and edge cases before they reach engineering.',
  },
  {
    number: '02',
    title: 'Plan the execution',
    body: 'A technical spec and task graph are produced automatically. Dependencies are mapped. Architecture decisions are explicit. The entire plan is reviewable before any code is written.',
  },
  {
    number: '03',
    title: 'Execute and ship',
    body: 'Autonomous agents execute tasks in isolated environments. Engineers review the output with full visibility into every decision. Approve, adjust, or take over at any point.',
  },
];
---

<section class="py-[120px] px-10 border-t border-border" id="how">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-[600px] mb-20">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-text-dim mb-5">How It Works</div>
      <h2 class="font-display heading-style text-[clamp(32px,4vw,48px)] leading-tight mb-5">
        Problem to PRD to pull request.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg leading-relaxed">
        You define the problem. Ultraviolet structures the plan, breaks it into tasks, and executes the code. Your engineers review and merge.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12 lg:gap-12">
      {steps.map((step) => (
        <div>
          <div class="font-display heading-style text-[64px] text-bg-tertiary leading-none mb-6">{step.number}</div>
          <h3 class="font-display heading-style text-2xl mb-4">{step.title}</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-base leading-relaxed">{step.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
